      • evaluate

        @RegionEffects(value="reads Instance, v0:Instance, v1:Instance")
public java.awt.geom.QuadCurve2D evaluate(java.awt.geom.QuadCurve2D v0,
                                                    java.awt.geom.QuadCurve2D v1,
                                                    double fraction)
        Description copied from interface: Evaluator
        Evaluates between two boundary values. Typically implementations use linear parametric evaluation: 
         v = v0 + (v1 - v0) * fraction
        Implementations of Evaluator will need to override this method and do something similar for their own types.

        Note that this mechanism may be used to create non-linear interpolators for specific value types, although it may be simpler to just use the linear/parametric interpolation technique here and perform non-linear interpolation through a custom Interpolator rather than perform custom calculations in this method. The point of this class is to allow calculations with new/unknown types, not to provide another mechanism for non-linear interpolation.
